abstract: The House tax bill championed by President Trump finds many different ways to increase inequality.
snippet: The House tax bill championed by President Trump finds many different ways to increase inequality.
lead_paragraph: As it stands now, the proposed House tax bill would give the undeserving rich — legatees who will inherit multimillion dollar estates — a $172.2 billion tax break over the next ten years. In doing so, the measure would further entrench the super rich, a class that in recent years has acquired a growing share of both income and wealth.

abstract: Now that the Murdochs have signaled an openness to selling assets, expect a host of potential suitors to try and persuade them to revive deal talks.
snippet: Now that the Murdochs have signaled an openness to selling assets, expect a host of potential suitors to try and persuade them to revive deal talks.
lead_paragraph: Good Tuesday morning. Rupert Murdoch and his sons have effectively put the bigger of their family empires, 21st Century Fox, in play. Will Disney come back, or will an entity like Apple swoop in instead? We’re also watching to see if Broadcom will go hostile in its $105 billion pursuit of Qualcomm. And we’re wondering if there will be more changes to the tax code after the introduction of restrictions on carried interest.

abstract: The detention of Prince Alwaleed and other top royals have introduced questions among investors over potential instability in the kingdom.
snippet: The detention of Prince Alwaleed and other top royals have introduced questions among investors over potential instability in the kingdom.
lead_paragraph: Good Monday morning. Andrew has thoughts on the detention of Prince Alwaleed of Saudi Arabia over the weekend, especially after interviewing the billionaire less than two weeks ago. And we’re looking at the fallout from the Paradise Papers leaks.

snippet: The failure of the talks marked the second time in three years that the two failed to reach a deal to create a stronger competitor to Verizon and AT&T.
lead_paragraph: Sprint and T-Mobile said on Saturday that they had ended merger talks, marking the second time in three years that the two failed to reach a deal to create a stronger competitor to Verizon and AT&T.
